    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the fish is cooked, transfer it to a clean board and return the pan and any <strong>remaining juices</strong> to a low heat</p><p>Add the <strong>harissa paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> to the pan and mix it all together</p><p>Squeeze in the<strong> </strong>juice of<strong> </strong>1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span><strong> lemon </strong>and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>warm harissa dressing</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon </strong>into wedges</p>",
